f=Cybersecurity/cortex/operational/tool/cortex-tool-requirements.md · h1:cortex — Tool Requirements=**Specifies needs; grant them.** Access configured deployment (Fleet Charter Rails 1–2). external call plan-locked sandboxed. · h1:cortex — Tool Requirements=\| Skill \| Needs \| Why \| · h1:cortex — Tool Requirements=\|---\|---\|---\| · h1:cortex — Tool Requirements=\| detection-engineering \| SIEM read access (Elastic/Splunk API); file read/write \| Fetch alerts, manage rules, document tuning \| · h1:cortex — Tool Requirements=\| security-monitoring \| SIEM read access; case management (if available); file read/write \| Triage queue, case tracking \| · h1:cortex — Tool Requirements=\| security-incident-response \| File read/write; evidence storage (file system); forensics tool access if available \| IR documentation, evidence preservation \| · h1:cortex — Tool Requirements=\| threat-hunting \| Log source read access (endpoint, network, cloud); hunting tool CLIs (if available) \| Data queries, tool execution \| · h2:Explicit non-needs hard prohibition (the security-inversion)=**NO execute access containment tools** (firewall, EDR isolate, IAM suspend, cloud block). cortex recommends containment; operator executes., **NO write access production systems security controls.** cortex writes case files investigative notes only., **No SIEM write access** rule changes detection rules modified through operator change management gate. · n=cortex detection response brain; read access everything write access almost nothing., SIEM read access single important technical dependency without it, operations manual.